@startuml 03_group_leader_workflow_dev
title BookRover — Group Leader Workflow (DEV)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam defaultFontSize 13

actor       "Group Leader\n(Browser)"     as GL
participant "React App\n(localhost:5173)" as FE
participant "FastAPI\n(localhost:8000)"   as BE
database    "DynamoDB\n(AWS / local)"     as DB

note over FE, BE
  **DEV environment variables required**
  FE: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
  BE: APP_ENV=dev
      BOOKROVER_TABLE_PREFIX=bookrover
      AWS_REGION, AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
end note

note over GL, FE
  Precondition: group leader is logged in.
  localStorage holds bookrover_token.
  AuthContext holds: group_leader_id, roles=["group_leader"]
  All requests carry: Authorization: Bearer <token>
end note

== Dashboard loads at /dashboard ==

FE    -> BE : GET /group-leaders/{group_leader_id}/dashboard\n?bookstore_id={bookstore_id}

note right of BE
  group_leader_id comes from AuthContext (GET /me response).
  First bookstore_id defaults to the first in the GL's bookstore_ids list.
end note

BE    -> DB : GetItem → bookrover-group-leaders-dev (GL record)
DB   --> BE : { group_leader_id, name, bookstore_ids[], ... }
BE    -> DB : GetItem → bookrover-bookstores-dev (selected bookstore)
DB   --> BE : { bookstore_id, store_name, ... }
BE    -> DB : Query sellers by group_leader_id + bookstore_id
DB   --> BE : [Seller records]

loop for each seller
    BE -> DB : Query sales by seller_id + bookstore_id
    DB --> BE : [Sale records]
    BE -> BE : Aggregate: total_books_sold, total_amount_collected per seller
end

BE   --> FE : 200 DashboardResponse\n{\n  group_leader: { name },\n  bookstore: { store_name },\n  sellers: [\n    { seller_name, total_books_sold,\n      total_amount_collected }\n  ],\n  totals: { grand_total_books, grand_total_amount }\n}

== View dashboard data ==

FE    -> FE : Render sellers table\n(columns: Seller Name, Books Sold, Money Collected)\nRender summary cards (total sellers, total amount)

== Sort sellers table ==

GL    -> FE : Click "Books Sold" or "Money Collected" column header
FE    -> FE : Toggle sort_by / sort_order\n(client-side sort — no API call)
FE    -> FE : Re-render sorted table

== Switch bookstore context (if multiple bookstores) ==

GL    -> FE : Click a different bookstore tab
FE    -> BE : GET /group-leaders/{group_leader_id}/dashboard\n?bookstore_id={new_bookstore_id}
BE    -> DB : Repeat fetch sequence for new bookstore
DB   --> BE : Fresh data for selected bookstore
BE   --> FE : 200 DashboardResponse (new bookstore context)
FE    -> FE : Re-render dashboard with new context

note over GL, DB
  **Read-only view** — the Group Leader cannot create, edit,
  or delete sellers, books, or sales. Those actions belong
  to the Admin (sellers/bookstores) and the Seller (inventory/sales).
end note

@enduml
